The paper proposes a novel data augmentation technique for deep neural networks that improves their performance and robustness. The tasks evaluated in the paper are related to computer vision (skin lesion classification and mammogram classification), suggesting that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as deep neural networks and generative adversarial networks, indicating that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves optimization techniques such as line-search manifold-exploration, which could place it in the optimization (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves medical imaging, which could place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
